main event: A witness reported seeing a bright orange, self-luminous object moving at high speed over Moss Bluff, Florida in March 1967.
interesting points: The object moved three times faster than a plane and gave off a bright glow.
The object appeared solid and seemed to stop in mid-air, change direction sharply, and then disappear.
The witness used binoculars, a telescope, and a movie camera to observe the object.
Other witnesses also reported seeing the object.
The witness estimated the object was about the size of a softball and half a mile away.
photographs: no, the report states there were no photographs taken
